Please answer the below core-java Questions:

Q. What is programing language?
A.a programming language is a language that allows us to write algorithms and computer programs that are understandable
by the machine (computer)

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What are the jdk components ? define each component?
A. JDK stands for java development kit, it contains development tools and the JRE (java runtime environment) as well as
 libraries and classes and the JVM (java virtual machine)

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is an IDE?
A.An IDE (integrated development environment) is software for creating applications, it facilitates the work of developers

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What are the IDEs available in the market to support java?
A.the IDEs available on the market to support java are: IntelliJ IDEA, Visual Studio, Eclipse, Xcode, NetBeans...etc.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. Explain the entire java life cycle.
A.the life cycle of Java begins by editing the program on a text editor or an IDE then compiling the source
code and transforming it into byte code in order to execute it

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is class?
A.A class is a template or blueprint that allows us to create objects and methods.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is object?
A.An object is an instance of a class

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is the entry point of an application?
A.The entry point of an application is main method

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. Why main method is static?
A.The main method is static because the compiler can call it without the creation of an object

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. Which class is the superclass of all classes in java?
A.java.lang.Object class is the super class for all classes

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is difference between path and classpath variables?
A.PATH is an environment variable that is used by the operating system to find executable files
  (javac.exe, java.exe, javadoc.exe, etc.)
  Classpath is an environment variable which is used by the compiler and the JVM to find the classpath.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is the difference between an Interface and Abstract class?
A.The interface supports multiple inheritance, abstract class doesn't support multiple inheritance, interface has only
static and final variables, abstract class can have final, non-final, static and non-static variables,
unlike the abstract class an interface can extend another Java interface only

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. Can you make an Object from an Interface and Abstract class ? how do you use interface and abstract class?
A.No, we can't create an object of an an interface and abstract class.
An interface can be implemented using keyword "implements".
An abstract class can be extended using keyword "extends".

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is Access Specifier?
A.Access specifier define the visibility of the class, method an object (public, private, protected and default)
private and protected cannot be used for classes

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is OOP ? Define each feature of java OOP.
A.OOP (Object-Oriented Programming) the main principles of OOP are : abstraction, encapsulation, inheritance, and polymorphism.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is Java Package and which package is imported by default?
A.the package consists of predefined java classes and interfaces, when we use these classes we must import
associated packages.
java.lang Package is imported by default.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is API? Name list of API that you have used so far.
A.APIs are mechanisms that allow two software components to communicate with each other using a set
of definitions and protocols

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. Does java support multiple inheritance?
A.Java doesnâ€™t support multiple inheritances

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is method overloading and when it happens?
A.method overloading is when two or more methods have the same name in the same class
this happens by changing the number of method arguments

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. Explain exceptions in java and how to handle it?
A. An exception occurs if there is an error while executing the program
we can use the try-catch method to handle exceptions

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is static keyword in java? How it has been used in variables, methods and classes?
A.static keyword is a non-access modifier, it is used for memory management. For example the static variable
can be used to refer to the common property of all objects and a static method can be invoked without the need
for creating an instance of a class.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is final and how it has been used variables, methods and classes?
A.Final is a keyword, it is a non-access specifier which is used to restrict a class, variable and method
if we use the final keyword with a variable : we cannot modify its value
if we use the final keyword with a method : it cannot be overridden by any subclasses
if we use the final keyword with a class :  we restrict the other classes to inherit it
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is final, finally and finalize?
A.- Final is a keyword, it is a non-access specifier which is used to restrict a class, variable and method
- The finally block executes when the try block exits, it is used to put important codes such as clean up code
- finalize() is a method, it allows to perform finalization operations, for example an operation of cleaning an object
before the Garbage Collector system takes care of it
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is a constructor ?
A.A constructor is used to initialize objects, it is called when an object of a class is created.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. Can we have multiple constructors in a class?
A.Yes

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. If we don't have a constructor declared, what is called during the object creation?
A.The default constructor is called during the object creation

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is "this" keyword in java ?
A."this" keyword refers to the current object in a method or constructor

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is "super" keyword in java? How to use it?
A."super" is used to call superclass methods and to access the superclass constructor

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is JVM stand for?
A.Java Virtual Machine

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. Is JVM platform independent?
A.Yes, JVM is platform independent. (Linux has a different JVM than Windows) that's why it supports portability

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What version of java are you using?
A.i use java 11

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is JAR stand for?
A.JAR stand for : Java ARchive

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is the difference between JDK and JVM?
A.JVM is a part of Java Run Environment (JRE) and JRE is a part of JDK
JDK contains tools required to write Java programs, and JRE to execute them.
JVM provides a platform-independent way of executing Java source code.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is the difference between JVM and JRE?
A.JVM is a part of Java Run Environment (JRE)
JVM provides a platform-independent way of executing Java source code.
JRE contains class libraries, JVM, and other supporting files

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is compile time and run time?
A.Compile time is the period when the programming code is converted to the binary code
Run time is the period of time when a program is running and occurs after compile time

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is the difference between String, StringBuffer and StringBuilder?
A.StringBuffer is thread-safe and synchronized whereas StringBuilder is not. String consumes more memory
as compared to the StringBuffer and StringBuilder
A String is immutable, StringBuffer and StringBuilder are mutable

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is Singleton class?
A.A singleton class is a class that can have only one object at a time

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is the difference between while and do..while loop?
A.do while loop execute the statements at least once, then the condition is checked
While loop checks the condition first and then executes the statements

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is Enum?
A.An enumeration is a special class that contains a group of constants

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is Iterator?
A.An Iterator is an object that can be used to loop through collections (ArrayList and HashSet)

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. Which one will take more memory, an int or Integer?
A.Integer take more memory
Integer size memory = 16 bytes
int size memory = 4 bytes

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is JIT stands for?
A.JIT stands for Java-In-Time Compiler

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. What is Recursion?
A.Recursion is the technique of making a method call itself (this is a way to implement a loop)
